        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1909796044" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5055858754783275379">Fan of exciting plot twists, suspense, and quick dialogue? <br/>This play is for you! <br/><br/>“Death and the Maiden” by Ariel Dorfman (1994) is an allegory for the Chilean revolution and aftermath of dictatorship. This play features three characters with quick tempers, shared histories, and intense character dynamics. It’s a short, fast read that you can finish in one sitting, so I definitely recommend even to the busiest of readers. <br/><br/>Enjoy!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


