<div id="review_3943841985" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3943841985" />
    <a title="Kristin Kharrat" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/122812052-kristin-kharrat"><img alt="Kristin Kharrat" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1626938729p2/122812052.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3943841985?book_show_action=true">Apr 14, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kristin Kharrat" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kristin Kharrat" href="/user/show/122812052-kristin-kharrat">Kristin Kharrat</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/122812052-kristin-kharrat?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3943841985" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5024393979665782909">I read this play for school and after annotating it thoroughly, I could not stop thinking about it. Ariel Dorfman is a master of intertwining the personal with the political, and he accurately portrays the fight between justice and reconciliation. I loved the ambiguity (I was so torn throughout the whole &quot;reading experience&quot;) in the play and the characters were extremely complex, which I also enjoyed. Dorfman&apos;s unusual use of some theatrical elements was extremely interesting and added so much t</span>
  <span id="freeText5024393979665782909" style="display:none">I read this play for school and after annotating it thoroughly, I could not stop thinking about it. Ariel Dorfman is a master of intertwining the personal with the political, and he accurately portrays the fight between justice and reconciliation. I loved the ambiguity (I was so torn throughout the whole "reading experience") in the play and the characters were extremely complex, which I also enjoyed. Dorfman's unusual use of some theatrical elements was extremely interesting and added so much to the fast-paced plot. Overall, this play is incredible and full of depth and detail. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5024393979665782909" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review3943841985">
