<div id="review_2808182448" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2808182448" />
    <a title="Cindy Leighton" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8801579-cindy-leighton"><img alt="Cindy Leighton" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1521331720p2/8801579.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2808182448?book_show_action=true">Jun 05, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cindy Leighton" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cindy Leighton" href="/user/show/8801579-cindy-leighton">Cindy Leighton</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8801579-cindy-leighton?shelf=latin-america">latin-america</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8801579-cindy-leighton?shelf=social-justice">social-justice</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2808182448" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11965309625611463096">Set in post-Pinochet Chile, or “a country that is probably Chile but could be any country that has given itself a democratic government just after a long period of dictatorship,” this play has only three characters and a sparse set - but delves into how a country and its people heal after living through state sponsored violence. Ignore? Punish? Retribution? Forgiveness? Who do you trust? Who do you believe?<br/><br/>Very intense play that absolutely could, unfortunately, be in any country that is trying t</span>
  <span id="freeText11965309625611463096" style="display:none">Set in post-Pinochet Chile, or “a country that is probably Chile but could be any country that has given itself a democratic government just after a long period of dictatorship,” this play has only three characters and a sparse set - but delves into how a country and its people heal after living through state sponsored violence. Ignore? Punish? Retribution? Forgiveness? Who do you trust? Who do you believe?<br /><br />Very intense play that absolutely could, unfortunately, be in any country that is trying to recover from brutal state sponsored violence. A man who has just been named to head the commission to look into the violence (now thirty years in the past) has a flat tire on his way home, and a doctor stops to help and gives him a ride home. When the doctor discovers who he is, the doctor stops by the house ostensibly to offer additional help. The man's wife believes she recognizes the doctor's voice and skin as a man who tortured and raped her repeatedly during the dictatorship. Who do you believe?<br /><br />Not very subtle or very nuanced - almost stereotypically "fiery." But the topic is not exactly one that lends itself to subtleties. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11965309625611463096" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


