<div id="review_2154079891" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2154079891" />
    <a title="Collin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4971265-collin"><img alt="Collin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1542214318p2/4971265.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2154079891?book_show_action=true">Oct 15, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Collin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Collin" href="/user/show/4971265-collin">Collin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audio CD 9781580816281" href="/book/show/7315461-death-and-the-maiden">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4971265-collin?shelf=drama">drama</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4971265-collin?shelf=2017-challenges">2017-challenges</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2154079891" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18440397407713640945">Intense and difficult. Definitely don&apos;t recommend for sensitive listeners or even listeners who might be sensitive. Paulina uses crude, angry, specific language to talk about her experiences and it&apos;s genuinely hard to listen to. <br/><br/>Still, it asks questions that need to be asked without giving easy answers, pointing out the cruelty of both the doctor then and Paulina now. You WANT Paulina to be justified, you want the narrative to justify her, and while it&apos;s true that the emotional truth IS that she</span>
  <span id="freeText18440397407713640945" style="display:none">Intense and difficult. Definitely don't recommend for sensitive listeners or even listeners who might be sensitive. Paulina uses crude, angry, specific language to talk about her experiences and it's genuinely hard to listen to. <br /><br />Still, it asks questions that need to be asked without giving easy answers, pointing out the cruelty of both the doctor then and Paulina now. You WANT Paulina to be justified, you want the narrative to justify her, and while it's true that the emotional truth IS that she's justified, morally she isn't; ethics are not driven by emotions. But doesn't Paulina deserve this? But isn't Roberto right, that no matter how her revenge is justified and deserved, it's still only more of the same and will beget another breed of cruelty, different but equally terrible?<br /><br />Tortured and honest. One of the very few times I've engaged in something this difficult to grapple and yet not regretted it, because of how necessary it is to hear.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18440397407713640945" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


