    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3483631989" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3483631989" />
    <a title="Ella  Myers" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/62783244-ella-myers"><img alt="Ella  Myers" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1609356632p2/62783244.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3483631989?book_show_action=true">Aug 07, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ella  Myers" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ella  Myers" href="/user/show/62783244-ella-myers">Ella  Myers</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3483631989" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1667510895859784278">Fascinating play that looks at the uneasy transition from dictatorship to democracy and the struggle between the victims who seek revenge for the torture they have experienced and the government who seeks to heal old wounds by not seeking retribution. Dorfman’s choice to explore these two perspectives in a married couple was an excellent one as the constant belittling of Paulina’s rage as female insanity chimed so well with the paternalistic attitude of lawyers like Gerardo who constantly remind</span>
  <span id="freeText1667510895859784278" style="display:none">Fascinating play that looks at the uneasy transition from dictatorship to democracy and the struggle between the victims who seek revenge for the torture they have experienced and the government who seeks to heal old wounds by not seeking retribution. Dorfman’s choice to explore these two perspectives in a married couple was an excellent one as the constant belittling of Paulina’s rage as female insanity chimed so well with the paternalistic attitude of lawyers like Gerardo who constantly remind victims to be sensible and think of the greater good instead of looking for revenge.<br /><br />I would highly recommend reading this play if you’re interested in Pinochet’s regime in Chile, pacifism and what happens after a dictatorship ends.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1667510895859784278" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review3483631989">
