<div id="review_3575649027" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3575649027" />
    <a title="mel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27178555-mel"><img alt="mel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1617457024p2/27178555.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3575649027?book_show_action=true">Oct 01, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="mel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="mel" href="/user/show/27178555-mel">mel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27178555-mel?shelf=school">school</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27178555-mel?shelf=plays">plays</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3575649027" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14914031159879080300">this is one of the best plays i&apos;ve read in quite some time. i love how simple the language was in discussing such dark, complex topics and i think dorfman did such a wonderful job of grounding the play in a setting that is universal and generic but still palpable and relatable. i love the complexity of paulina&apos;s character and i think it was such a strong choice for the audience to never actually discover whether or not roberto is innocent. the incorporation of music was so clever. i&apos;m really wis</span>
  <span id="freeText14914031159879080300" style="display:none">this is one of the best plays i've read in quite some time. i love how simple the language was in discussing such dark, complex topics and i think dorfman did such a wonderful job of grounding the play in a setting that is universal and generic but still palpable and relatable. i love the complexity of paulina's character and i think it was such a strong choice for the audience to never actually discover whether or not roberto is innocent. the incorporation of music was so clever. i'm really wishing i could see this live because i can only imagine how breathtaking the mirror scene must be in person. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14914031159879080300" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


