<div id="review_4115865421" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4115865421" />
    <a title="DS Coremans" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/118810855-ds-coremans"><img alt="DS Coremans" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1600163441p2/118810855.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4115865421?book_show_action=true">Jul 15, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="DS Coremans" class="user" itemprop="url" name="DS Coremans" href="/user/show/118810855-ds-coremans">DS Coremans</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781854593900" href="/book/show/249150.Death_And_The_Maiden">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4115865421" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3747470151719265005">Dorfman in this short play offers an insight into the ambiguous nature of power and balance, or truth and the impact which it has on in an ever evolving global society. Still very relevant and not just to the political realities of post-democratic Chilean life, Death and the Maiden is a poignant read which brings our immediate past into focus, branding it with a spotlight in order to address internally how a future is only possible when we as individuals take responsibility for our own lives and</span>
  <span id="freeText3747470151719265005" style="display:none">Dorfman in this short play offers an insight into the ambiguous nature of power and balance, or truth and the impact which it has on in an ever evolving global society. Still very relevant and not just to the political realities of post-democratic Chilean life, Death and the Maiden is a poignant read which brings our immediate past into focus, branding it with a spotlight in order to address internally how a future is only possible when we as individuals take responsibility for our own lives and the part we play within them.<br /><br />DSC<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.fodibyli.com">www.fodibyli.com</a><br />#FoDiByLi</span>
  <a data-text-id="3747470151719265005" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


