        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4122603067" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9188581633936021247">I think one should distinguish between those who first saw Polanski&apos;s film and then read the book, and those who first read Drufman&apos;s book after Polanski&apos;s film. The book slowly penetrates the reader&apos;s soul and the film suddenly erupts the woman Therefore, this gentle influence of the book has a more intense effect on the reader. Just like the difference between a chronic pain and an immediate pain. In Polanski&apos;s film, with a few screams and a few punches and kicks, the woman is relieved of grie</span>
  <span id="freeText9188581633936021247" style="display:none">I think one should distinguish between those who first saw Polanski's film and then read the book, and those who first read Drufman's book after Polanski's film. The book slowly penetrates the reader's soul and the film suddenly erupts the woman Therefore, this gentle influence of the book has a more intense effect on the reader. Just like the difference between a chronic pain and an immediate pain. In Polanski's film, with a few screams and a few punches and kicks, the woman is relieved of grief, but in The book seems to be eternal pain and horror.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9188581633936021247" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

