<div id="review_2233095177" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2233095177" />
    <a title="Mary Beth" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6433152-mary-beth"><img alt="Mary Beth" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1393001617p2/6433152.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2233095177?book_show_action=true">Dec 30, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mary Beth" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mary Beth" href="/user/show/6433152-mary-beth">Mary Beth</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6433152-mary-beth?shelf=plays">plays</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2233095177" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10138718266574350349">The ambiguous truth and intractable horror of <i>Maiden</i> are stomach-churning, for Dorfman offers neither audience nor reader any easy answers. And in the midst of it all, Paulina, as bold and unrelenting as a Fury, is a provocative, powerfully indelible character. Her fierce, eloquent monologues are the heart of the play.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

